Description:
Stylish & Spacious Sophistication with your own 5-6 car basement!

Close to shops, schools & station...you'll need to see this to believe it!

Description:
Sized to Surprise with Further Aspirations
Well proportioned retaining its warmth and character, this generous 4 bedroom 2 bathroom family home is new where it counts and opens your imagination around every corner.
On 700sqm approx with potential to subdivide (STCA), extend or landscape in spectacular style, this family gem enjoys a wide entry hall, 4 good size bedrooms (2 with fitted BIRs, one with OFP), a stunning new kitchen with Caesarstone benchtops & Blanco stainless steel appliances, casual family living & dining with bi-fold doors to the east-facing rear garden, stylish family bathroom, 2nd bathroom adjoining the fitted laundry and an enormous rumpus room upstairs (home theatre provision).
An excellent opportunity to add your own sense of style, complete with ducted heating, evaporative cooling, ducted vac, temperature controlled hot water (3 points), timber blinds, polished boards (Baltic pine and hardwood) and a large workshed.
In the sought after McKinnon Secondary College zone, as easy walk to North Road shops, restaurants & the train, funky McKinnon Village cafes and the Monash Uni/Elwood Beach bus.

Stunning Californian, A Must See
Enter off Wild Cherry Road.
Fall in love with this captivating 4 bedroom, 2 bathroom tuck-pointed brick Californian Bungalow. Description:
Period Perfection in Blue-Chip Ormond!
Character-filled and fresco-focused, this immaculate Californian Bungalow family home is an accommodating entertainer in the heart of blue-chip Ormond! Period perfection dominates, with fretwork, ornate high ceilings, leadlight & polished boards featuring through four bedrooms (3 doubles with BIRs), two bathrooms, formal lounge & dining (OFP) & a bay-windowed home office/study. Stylishly integrated with ducted heating & evap. cooling, a Smeg-applianced blackwood kitchen & sunny family room open out to established rear gardens with a built-in BBQ & sail covered entertaining. Surrounded by quality homes in a tightly-held street, there's a tandem carport for OSP, but simply step outside & be moments from shops, station, schools & EE Gunn Reserve!.. Note: Heritage Overlay

SOLD by Tom Grieve
Plans & Permits approved to retain the existing home and develop two double storey townhouses in the rear yard.
Enjoying a deep 50.29m/165ft approx. block, this mesmerising 4 bedroom + study 2 bathroom Californian Bungalow has all the warmth and charm of a relaxed family home.
Gorgeous with its leadlight windows, high strapped ceilings, open fireplace and dormer windows, this engaging treasure enjoys a lovely sitting room (OFP), downstairs main bedroom, tasteful bathroom, stunning dining area with French doors onto the deck and capturing the glorious garden view, 2nd downstairs bedroom, large study and a fresh white kitchen with WI pantry, 5 burner gas stove and Bosch dishwasher with garden windows, & laundry.
Upstairs, is the children's domain with its attic style retreat (storage), 2 large bedrooms (BIRs & plantation shutters) and a sparkling bathroom.
A lovely home that's perfect for entertaining, complete with polished boards, ducted heating, air conditioner and an alarm. An excellent family location, just metres to the bus, train, leading schools, a great selection of cafes and beautiful parks.

Description:
Period character, perfect locale & opportunity
Retaining all the charm & warmth synonymous with its 1920s heritage, beyond the timber front porch sits a traditional central hallway, formal living & dining area complemented by 10ft ceilings and further enhanced by lead light windows. The home features two bedrooms, an elevated light filled sunroom, original kitchen and separate bathroom. Against a backdrop of a winning address with St Kevin's Primary School at the end of the street, Ormond & McKinnon train stations within easy walking distance and firmly entrenched within the McKinnon Secondary College zone enticing opportunities don't come much better than this. Set on approx 697sqm, there's scope to renovate & extend the dimensions into the rear yard currently home to an outside laundry, garden shed and single lock-up garage. Take your cues from the other Californian Bungalow style homes that dominate the area before exploring the options and establish an enviable future in this highly desirable location without fear of overcapitalising!

Description:
***UNDER OFFER*** Zoned period grace
From its impressive elevated presence set back from the road, with a wide frontage, to its pride of place in the McKinnon College Zone, this character laden Californian Bungalow retains all the warmth and rich detailing synonymous with its origins from double entry glass etched doors to finished timber door frames and high ornate ceilings. Stepping beyond its lovely front decked porch, you'll find a grand formal living space (tiled open fire place & a lavish leadlight bay window) opening into adjoining dining with a gas log fire complemented by original Baltic pine flooring. While enjoying early 19th century origins, it has been updated for the modern family offering four bedroom accommodation & a central timber kitchen flowing into casual entertaining which opens onto a spacious undercover alfresco deck via bi-folding doors. All of this is set in a lovely established garden, in a peaceful street with low traffic flow within strolling distance of shops, station, quality parks, public transport & further enhanced by ducted gas heating, RC air conditioning, period style bathroom, ample off street parking, garden shed, second shower, separate WC & laundry.
